<HEADLINE>
HAKKA FOOD CULTURE FESTIVAL OPENS IN TAICHUNG
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taichung,  May 18 (CNA) 05/18/07  22:10:59 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
A Hakka food culture festival opened in Taichung Friday to allow
residents in the central Taiwan city to find out more about Hakka
cuisine and other aspects of Hakka culture.
</P>
<P>
Taichung Deputy Mayor Hsiao Chia-chi and Huang Jui-ju, deputy
chairman of the Cabinet-level Council for Hakka Affairs, jointly
presided over the opening ceremony for the three-day event at the
Taichung central shopping mall near the Taichung railway station.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said that in addition to the opportunity to taste
Hakka delicacies, visitors can buy handicrafts and other products
featuring a Hakka motif, as well as books and CDs on Hakka
culture.
</P>
<P>
Visitors can also enjoy various performances, including Hakka
folk songs, dances and short plays,  while schoolchildren can
participate in a wooden duck-painting contest, according to the
organizers.
</P>
